Now, if I can, uh,

27:50.274 --> 27:52.007
offer you a word of advice...

27:52.009 --> 27:53.375
Mm-hmm?

27:53.377 --> 27:55.010
I would consider
wrapping this whole thing up.

27:55.012 --> 27:56.378
Uh, what do you mean?

27:56.380 --> 27:58.547
I mean the whole
living arrangement.

27:58.549 --> 28:01.116
The kids, the girls,
the beach house.

28:01.118 --> 28:05.154
I mean, this whole thing
has been going on way too long.

28:06.189 --> 28:09.091
Yeah, a lot of people
been saying that.

28:09.093 --> 28:11.393
Haters gonna hate.

28:13.963 --> 28:15.764
♪ <i>Men.</i> ♪

28:15.766 --> 28:18.033
We should get out of town
for a couple of days.

28:18.035 --> 28:19.735
You know, go to
a nice resort,

28:19.737 --> 28:21.704
uh, get some facials,
Mani-pedis.

28:21.706 --> 28:23.272
You know, a
guys' weekend.

28:23.274 --> 28:25.140
No... we're not going anywhere.

28:25.142 --> 28:27.276
We got a state-of-the-art
security system.

28:27.278 --> 28:30.446
Nobody gets in
unless we let them in.

28:31.481 --> 28:33.649
(both screaming)

28:35.518 --> 28:38.587
What the hell?

28:38.589 --> 28:40.489
"We got a state-of-the-art
security system.

28:40.491 --> 28:42.524
No one gets in unless
we let them in."

28:42.526 --> 28:44.560
Shut up.
No, you shut up.

28:44.562 --> 28:46.428
Hey.
- (both scream)

28:52.802 --> 28:54.436
Jake?
- Oh, my God. Oh, my God!

28:54.438 --> 28:55.671
Oh, my God.

28:55.673 --> 28:56.772
(laughing)

28:56.774 --> 28:58.440
Hey!

28:58.442 --> 28:59.641
What are you
doing here?

28:59.643 --> 29:01.343
Yeah, I thought
you were in the Army.

29:01.345 --> 29:02.711
Come on. Look at me.

29:02.713 --> 29:05.280
Do I look like someone
who's in the Army?

29:05.282 --> 29:06.548
Not on our side.

29:08.318 --> 29:10.919
Come in.

29:10.921 --> 29:13.956
Hey. These are pretty cool.
Where'd you get them? Target?

29:13.958 --> 29:15.424
(laughs)

29:15.426 --> 29:17.126
You get it? 'Cause of the...
there's the circles...

29:17.128 --> 29:19.194
Yeah, no, no, I got it.
I got it. No.

29:19.196 --> 29:20.496
Here's the thing.

29:20.498 --> 29:22.164
It turns out that
your Uncle Charlie

29:22.166 --> 29:23.565
might still be alive.

29:23.567 --> 29:24.900
Oh.

29:24.902 --> 29:28.203
That would explain why
I got a check for $250,000

29:28.205 --> 29:30.606
and a note that said,
"I'm alive."

29:31.708 --> 29:33.876
You have $250,000?

29:33.878 --> 29:36.178
Not anymore. I stopped in
in Vegas on the way here.

29:36.180 --> 29:38.480
Oh, God. How much
do you have left?

29:38.482 --> 29:40.516
Two and a half million.

29:40.518 --> 29:42.084
(whimpers)

29:42.086 --> 29:43.519
Oh!

29:43.521 --> 29:46.522
You won $2.5 million?

29:46.524 --> 29:48.090
Oh, yeah.
It's not that hard.

29:48.092 --> 29:51.326
I kept playing craps
because, you know, "crap."

29:52.896 --> 29:55.063
Oh, and I kept
betting on come, because...

29:55.065 --> 29:57.900
(laughing)

29:57.902 --> 30:02.104
Wow. That's... amazing
that you made so much money

30:02.106 --> 30:04.239
with such stupid jokes.

30:11.214 --> 30:12.214
Taterhead!

30:13.917 --> 30:15.317
Hey, Berta.

30:15.319 --> 30:17.219
Oh, look at you!

30:17.221 --> 30:18.954
You look like a grown man.

30:18.956 --> 30:21.056
Really? Which one?

30:21.058 --> 30:23.225
I've missed you.

30:23.227 --> 30:24.893
Berta, what are you
still doing here?

30:24.895 --> 30:26.228
No idea.

30:27.964 --> 30:29.865
By the way, you're out of pot.

30:31.634 --> 30:33.569
Where'd these things come from?
Target?

30:33.571 --> 30:34.571
JAKE:
Ah.

30:34.572 --> 30:35.704
Too late.

30:35.706 --> 30:37.306
I already did that joke.
Ah...

30:37.308 --> 30:38.574
No, somebody
left them here.

30:38.576 --> 30:39.808
You didn't
hear anything?

30:39.810 --> 30:41.243
I heard colors.

30:41.245 --> 30:43.145
No, I-I am telling you,

30:43.147 --> 30:45.647
Charlie is planning
on killing us all.

30:45.649 --> 30:47.549
Okay. It was good
to see you guys.

30:47.551 --> 30:49.551
Wait, Th-that's it?
You're leaving?

30:49.553 --> 30:51.854
Oh, nothing personal--
I just got to get back to Japan

30:51.856 --> 30:53.922
and tell my wife and kids
that we're rich.

30:53.924 --> 30:55.591
You're...
you're married?

30:55.593 --> 30:56.925
Yeah. Didn't I mention that?

30:56.927 --> 30:57.927
No.

30:57.928 --> 30:59.895
Wh-Wh-Wh-Whoa.
You have kids?

30:59.897 --> 31:01.129
Well, they're hers.

31:01.131 --> 31:02.431
She's a dancer.

31:02.433 --> 31:04.333
Uh, let me guess--
a pole dancer?

31:04.335 --> 31:06.301
No, she's Japanese.

31:14.010 --> 31:16.111
Well, see you.

31:18.748 --> 31:20.816
All right, all right, we-we
got to close these shades.

31:20.818 --> 31:23.085
Anybody on the beach will
have a clear shot at us.

31:23.087 --> 31:24.253
Right.

31:24.255 --> 31:26.054
Do this...

31:29.192 --> 31:32.427
Man, it sucks to be you guys.

31:33.830 --> 31:35.597
♪ <i>Men.</i> ♪

31:35.599 --> 31:37.032
(phone ringing)

31:37.034 --> 31:38.500
Hello?

31:38.502 --> 31:39.868
Judith, it's me.

31:39.870 --> 31:41.136
Oh, hey, Alan.

31:41.138 --> 31:42.671
Isn't it wonderful about Jake?

31:42.673 --> 31:43.939
Uh, yeah, wonderful.
Listen...

31:43.941 --> 31:45.707
Did he give you $100,000, too?

31:45.709 --> 31:47.309
He gave you $100,000?

31:47.311 --> 31:48.977
No. What do you want?

31:50.013 --> 31:51.847
Uh, uh, okay, long story short--

31:51.849 --> 31:54.950
it turns out my brother is alive
and he's out for revenge.

31:54.952 --> 31:56.585
Revenge? For what?

31:56.587 --> 31:58.921
Well, he didn't think
I could go on without him.

31:58.923 --> 32:00.255
He thought I was more of

32:00.257 --> 32:02.024
a supporting character
in his life,

32:02.026 --> 32:04.526
but it turns out
I-I was sort of a co-lead.

32:04.528 --> 32:07.396
Um, a-anyway,
I just wanted you to know

32:07.398 --> 32:09.698
that if anything
were to happen to me,

32:09.700 --> 32:11.700
you were the love of my life.

32:11.702 --> 32:13.835
Oh, Alan, that is so sweet.

32:13.837 --> 32:16.572
Hang on, honey.
I'm getting another call.

32:25.915 --> 32:27.716
She's not coming back.

32:27.718 --> 32:29.484
♪ <i>Men.</i> ♪

32:29.486 --> 32:31.086
(phone ringing)

32:31.088 --> 32:32.421
Hello?

32:32.423 --> 32:33.889
Bridget, hi.

32:33.891 --> 32:35.324
It's Walden.

32:35.326 --> 32:37.225
Hey, Walden. What's up?

32:37.227 --> 32:40.028
I can't go into detail,
but I just...

32:40.030 --> 32:43.231
I wanted to say that I wish
I'd been a better husband.

32:43.233 --> 32:44.566
(chuckles softly)

32:44.568 --> 32:46.668
Well, thank you.

32:46.670 --> 32:49.137
And I just want to say that...

32:49.139 --> 32:51.039
I'm having sex with John Stamos.

32:53.610 --> 32:54.610
I'm not lying.

32:54.612 --> 32:56.478
(snaps fingers)

32:56.480 --> 32:58.680
Go for Stamos.

32:58.682 --> 33:00.882
Stamos, you're just
a handsome guy

33:00.884 --> 33:02.918
who got lucky on a sitcom.

33:02.920 --> 33:05.387
Listen, um, I'm just gonna
set the phone down

33:05.389 --> 33:07.923
so you can listen to me
shish-kebab your old lady, okay?

33:07.925 --> 33:09.124
Bye-bye.

33:09.126 --> 33:11.126
♪ <i>Men.</i> ♪

33:11.128 --> 33:12.461
(photographers clamoring)

33:12.463 --> 33:15.297
(phone ringing)
Hold on, fellas.

33:15.299 --> 33:17.099
Hello.

33:17.101 --> 33:18.600
Uh, Kandi, it's Alan.

33:18.602 --> 33:20.769
Oh, hi, Alan!

33:20.771 --> 33:22.337
I just wanted you to know that,

33:22.339 --> 33:24.473
even though we were only married
for a short time,

33:24.475 --> 33:26.808
you were the love of my life.

33:26.810 --> 33:28.510
Oh, how sweet.

33:28.512 --> 33:31.947
And you were the first guy
I had tushy sex with.

33:31.949 --> 33:33.949
You guys didn't hear that.

33:33.951 --> 33:35.083
♪ <i>Men.</i> ♪

33:35.085 --> 33:36.284
(phone ringing)

33:36.286 --> 33:37.519
Hello.

33:37.521 --> 33:38.954
Zoey.

33:38.956 --> 33:41.123
Hi. It's Walden.

33:41.125 --> 33:43.025
Oh, Walden.

33:43.027 --> 33:45.327
How are you, darling?

33:45.329 --> 33:47.162
Uh, not so good.

33:47.164 --> 33:49.031
Uh... that's why I'm calling.

33:49.033 --> 33:51.700
I... I just wanted
to tell you that...

33:51.702 --> 33:54.436
I've been thinking
about you lately, and...

33:54.438 --> 33:56.805
I'm sorry about
the way things ended.

33:56.807 --> 33:59.708
Oh, well...
water under the bridge.

33:59.710 --> 34:01.510
Listen, I'd love to chat,

34:01.512 --> 34:03.278
but I'm in the middle
of a coronation.

34:06.516 --> 34:08.617
Of a what?

34:08.619 --> 34:10.185
A coronation.

34:10.187 --> 34:12.154
I married King Rupert
of Moldavia,

34:12.156 --> 34:15.157
and I'm being
crowned queen, so...

34:15.159 --> 34:18.159
You're the queen of Moldavia?

34:18.161 --> 34:19.728
What can I say?

34:19.730 --> 34:21.329
Thank you, JDate.

34:21.331 --> 34:23.565
(sighs) Shalom.

34:26.235 --> 34:28.437
Darling,
you still breathing?

34:28.438 --> 34:30.072
♪ <i>Men.</i> ♪

34:30.074 --> 34:31.373
Hello?

34:31.375 --> 34:32.741
Lyndsey, it's Alan.

34:32.743 --> 34:33.942
Hi, Alan.

34:33.944 --> 34:35.243
I was just showing off

34:35.245 --> 34:36.885
the beautiful engagement ring
you gave me.

34:39.181 --> 34:41.717
Great. Listen,
I-I just wanted you to know

34:41.719 --> 34:44.186
that if anything
were to happen to me,

34:44.188 --> 34:46.188
you were the love of my life.

34:46.190 --> 34:47.789
Oh, baby.

34:47.791 --> 34:49.824
You're the love of my life.

34:49.827 --> 34:51.092
(quietly):
So, how much?

34:53.062 --> 34:54.862
♪ <i>Men.</i> ♪

34:54.864 --> 34:56.864
Okay, I will say
it one more time.

34:56.867 --> 34:58.600
Resort hotel
till the cops find him.

34:58.602 --> 35:00.802
We can be in Vegas in two hours.

35:00.804 --> 35:03.205
Styx is playing Mandalay Bay.

35:03.207 --> 35:05.540
No, if I let Charlie
drive me out of this house,

35:05.542 --> 35:07.743
I reward his bad behavior.

35:07.745 --> 35:10.712
Yeah. That's only supposed
to happen in show business.

35:10.714 --> 35:11.847
Which we are not in.

35:11.849 --> 35:15.383
Not anymore.

35:15.385 --> 35:17.652
(cell phone ringing)

35:17.654 --> 35:20.088
Oh. Hello?

35:20.090 --> 35:22.224
Valden?
Walden.

35:22.226 --> 35:24.359
That's what I said.

35:24.361 --> 35:26.394
Look, I have good news.

35:26.396 --> 35:27.629
We found your boy.

35:27.631 --> 35:28.764
They found Charlie.

35:28.766 --> 35:30.065
Are-are they sure?

35:30.067 --> 35:31.967
Uh, uh, are...
are you sure it's him?

35:31.969 --> 35:33.969
Well, he matches
the description.

35:33.971 --> 35:36.271
Bowling shirt, cargo shorts,

35:36.273 --> 35:38.373
and he's babbling away
incoherently.

35:39.408 --> 35:40.408
That sounds like him.

35:40.410 --> 35:41.410
Wh-Where'd you find him?

35:41.411 --> 35:42.711
In a trashed hotel room

35:42.713 --> 35:44.379
with a hooker in the closet.

35:44.381 --> 35:46.081
That's absolutely him.

35:46.083 --> 35:47.649
Oh, my...
Thank you so much.

35:47.651 --> 35:49.417
This is a huge relief.

35:49.419 --> 35:50.685
Oh, you're welcome.

35:50.687 --> 35:52.053
Uh, see you in the gym.

35:52.055 --> 35:54.356
Okay. Hasta la vista.

35:54.358 --> 35:57.425
I'm telling you,
I'm not Charlie Harper.

35:57.427 --> 35:58.660
Then who are you?

35:58.662 --> 36:00.862
My name is Christian Slater.

36:00.864 --> 36:02.731
I'm an actor, all right?

36:02.733 --> 36:05.200
I was in a bar, and this guy
hands me a drink.

36:05.202 --> 36:07.469
Next thing I know,
I wake up in a hotel room

36:07.471 --> 36:08.637
dressed like a 12-year-old,

36:08.639 --> 36:10.839
with a screaming woman
in the closet.

36:10.841 --> 36:12.007
Yeah, right.

36:12.009 --> 36:13.742
And I'm the governor
of California.

36:15.178 --> 36:17.479
That bitch stole my watch.

36:17.481 --> 36:19.881
♪ <i>Men.</i> ♪

36:27.352 --> 36:29.820
♪ <i>Men.</i> ♪

36:29.822 --> 36:31.455
What do you think
Charlie will do

36:31.457 --> 36:32.856
when he gets out
of jail?

36:32.858 --> 36:35.759
Well, if the past
is any indication,

36:35.761 --> 36:39.463
he'll sober up and reflect
on his past mistakes,

36:39.465 --> 36:41.098
apologize to everyone,

36:41.100 --> 36:43.000
and then do something
even worse.

36:44.769 --> 36:46.637
See, I'm not so pessimistic.

36:46.639 --> 36:48.905
I'm hoping someday
he and I can be buddies.

36:52.010 --> 36:54.011
(all laughing)

36:55.513 --> 36:58.148
Good one.

36:58.150 --> 36:59.483
By the way,

36:59.485 --> 37:01.885
when this cigar is done,
so am I.

37:01.887 --> 37:03.620
Yeah, you calling it a day?

37:03.622 --> 37:05.355
Calling it a career.

37:05.357 --> 37:06.456
You're quitting?

37:06.458 --> 37:08.458
I didn't want to rub
your nose in it,

37:08.460 --> 37:10.394
but Charlie sent me
a big-ass check,

37:10.396 --> 37:11.862
so I'm out of here.

37:11.864 --> 37:13.196
Where you gonna go?

37:13.198 --> 37:14.498
Don't know.

37:14.500 --> 37:16.133
Somewhere the sun is bright,

37:16.135 --> 37:19.202
the pot is strong
and the men are stupid.

37:20.338 --> 37:21.872
That's here.

37:24.242 --> 37:25.942
You're right.

37:25.944 --> 37:27.511
I'm staying.

37:29.380 --> 37:30.747
(helicopter whirring overhead)

37:30.749 --> 37:31.915
Wow.

37:31.917 --> 37:33.717
Look at that.

37:36.954 --> 37:39.856
Someone's having a piano
delivered by helicopter.

37:39.858 --> 37:42.025
Mmm. That's the kind
of extravagant thing

37:42.027 --> 37:43.593
Charlie would do.

37:43.595 --> 37:46.129
Oh, uh, he had a baby grand
just like that.

37:46.131 --> 37:47.731
It's coming right this way.

37:49.434 --> 37:51.968
You don't think
that it's possible

37:51.970 --> 37:54.638
that the cops got
the wrong guy, do you?

37:56.541 --> 37:58.575
Nah.
- Nah.

38:06.184 --> 38:07.584
(rings doorbell)

38:07.586 --> 38:09.086
(helicopter whirring overhead)

38:19.999 --> 38:21.733
Winning.

